        <h3>3.3.5 Bladder Dysfunction</h3>

        <p>
            Approximately 75% of people with MS experience some type of bladder dysfunction during the 
            course of their disease. The effect of this can be difficult for the person, since bladder 
            control may deteriorate at the same time as mobility worsens, making it increasingly difficult 
            to respond to bladder urgency by hurrying to the toilet.
        </p>

        <div class="keypoint">
            Approximately 75% of people with MS experience some type of bladder dysfunction during 
            the course of their disease.
        </div>

        <p>
            There are three types of bladder dysfunction most commonly associated with MS<sup>58</sup>.
            They are summarised in Table 2.
        </p>

